message.content: cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CL. The paper discusses methods and routines for analyzing and organizing scientific literature using citation and MeSH data, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Specifically, the paper's focus on clustering and mapping knowledge representations aligns with information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of matrices and main-path analysis could also be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's exploration of using MeSH terms as an alternative to WoS Subject Categories could be relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
